<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{y}={75}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{y}=-{99}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({9},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{1}{y}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={75}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{75}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{\left(\frac{{{75}-{\left({1}{y}\right)}}}{{9}}\right)}+{9}{y}=-{99}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{5}}{{9}}\cdot{\left({75}\right)}--\frac{{5}}{{9}}{\left({1}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}=-{99}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{41.666666666667}-{\left({0.55555555555556}\right)}{y}+{9}{y}=-{99}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.55555555555556}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}=-{99}--{41.666666666667}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.55555555555556}{y}+{\left({9}\right)}{y}=-{57.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({0.55555555555556}+{\left({9}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{57.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9.5555555555556}{y}=-{57.333333333333}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{57.333333333333}}{{9.5555555555556}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{1}{\left(-{6}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={75}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={81}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{81}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({9},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
